WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:07.190
Hello everybody. I'm Brandon Biggs, and this is Diana Biggs, and welcome to today's broadcast.

00:00:07.191 --> 00:00:18.218
I told you all for my birthday one year, the Lord said, 'I want to give you a little present.'I was in prayer, and I was just seeking Him.

00:00:18.219 --> 00:00:27.560
He said, 'I want to show you something.'All of a sudden, I was interceding for my birthday, and I was seeing in the spirit.

00:00:27.561 --> 00:00:33.947
I saw these beautiful mountains with snow caps on the top of them.

00:00:33.947 --> 00:00:39.039
They looked like the Swiss Alps—absolutely beautiful mountains.

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:46.729
There was a green valley with grass that was just the most beautiful, translucent-looking grass.

00:00:46.730 --> 00:00:52.767
It was gorgeous grass with flowers, like a meadow with butterflies.

00:00:52.768 --> 00:01:00.716
It was just the most beautiful backdrop with these mountains, a lake, and this beautiful scenery all around.

00:01:00.717 --> 00:01:10.602
Diana was doing cartwheels, and the Lord said, 'This is moments after the Rapture.'We were standing there in heaven.

00:01:10.603 --> 00:01:21.314
I was a young man; I looked a lot younger and I had hair. I had a glorified body, and Diana had her glorified body.

00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:29.916
She said, 'Brandon, we made it! We made it!'She was doing cartwheels, and she was just rejoicing and running through this meadow.

00:01:29.918 --> 00:01:36.522
It was green all around, with a beautiful green hill, and she was running and rejoicing.

00:01:36.523 --> 00:01:49.286
It was just so beautiful. I was breathing in the beautiful atmosphere of heaven for the very first time.

00:01:49.287 --> 00:02:01.999
Whenever you get to a hotel room or go to a place on vacation where you've never been, you want to see everything and all the sights around because you're just excited to be there.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:10.150
Multiply that by a billion. That's what this felt like: we made it.

00:02:10.151 --> 00:02:18.714
And the temperature—I remember I could feel it—it was like I was there.

00:02:18.715 --> 00:02:27.839
The atmosphere was about 65 to 70 degrees. It wasn't hot, but it wasn't cold. It was a perfect temperature.

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:34.392
Everything was perfect, and you could see those mountains, and it was just beautiful.

00:02:34.393 --> 00:02:43.535
I want to tell you all, heaven is a real place. Most people go, 'Well, is it?'No, I've seen it.

00:02:43.536 --> 00:02:52.388
I've been there. I've seen it—it is a massive, planet-like place. It is humongous.

00:02:52.389 --> 00:03:06.717
When I was taken back and I was coming to the Earth, it was in a ripple, how He had it hidden.

00:03:06.718 --> 00:03:19.052
It was a massive place, like three times the size of Jupiter, and there was no darkness at all.

00:03:19.053 --> 00:03:27.956
Everything was glowing. There were no shadows because there is no darkness.

00:03:27.957 --> 00:03:40.748
How do you explain that to somebody? Because all we know are shadows—there are shadows on the table.

00:03:40.749 --> 00:03:50.519
But there, there is no darkness. Everything is beautiful. Then one day I was praying, and the Lord told me to tell you all about this.

00:03:50.520 --> 00:04:02.699
That's how that basically ended; He allowed me to see Diana doing the cartwheels, and I was just looking over the horizon at the beauty of an area of heaven.

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:13.963
I don't know if my house was nearby there or not, but I wouldn't mind it in that green valley, by that lake, and those mountains with the snow tops.

00:04:13.964 --> 00:04:20.100
The things He has for every single one of you! If you only knew how much He loves you.

00:04:20.101 --> 00:04:27.568
If you just read your Bible and look at whenever it says that God is love, God loves you.

00:04:27.569 --> 00:04:37.242
He gave His one and only begotten Son, that whosoever believes in Him should not perish but have everlasting life.

00:04:37.243 --> 00:04:43.541
Every single one of us has an opportunity today to say yes to Jesus and no to hell.

00:04:43.542 --> 00:04:53.839
Every single one of us. You have a hell to shun and a heaven to gain. Rodney Howard-Browne talks about that.

00:04:53.840 --> 00:05:00.091
But I just want to encourage you all that when we go in the Rapture...

00:05:00.092 --> 00:05:10.648
I was praying one day, just like I always do. I said, 'Lord, what are you up to today? What is going on with you?'—just being personal with Him.

00:05:10.649 --> 00:05:18.743
And He said, 'Brandon, I'm going to show you what I'm doing.'He opened up a portal above me.

00:05:18.744 --> 00:05:35.191
It was a beautiful portal, and Jesus looked out through that portal and said, 'I'm going to show you what I'm doing today.'Just like that, right up here. All of a sudden, I went into that portal in the spirit.

00:05:35.192 --> 00:05:59.344
I went into that portal that He opened up above our living room, and I could see millions of plate settings that stretched forever, lined up on these beautiful tables.

00:05:59.345 --> 00:06:10.548
I'm talking beautiful wood tables with a gloss on them, not cheap plastic tables from Walmart.

00:06:10.549 --> 00:06:30.846
Each one of them had a name tag prepared for each one of us. There was a doily in the middle, and beautiful fine china with golden lace around it.

00:06:30.847 --> 00:06:48.363
It was all specifically designed for you out of the desires of your heart—the things that you find beautiful and attractive, things where you go, 'Wow, that makes me so happy, Lord.

00:06:48.364 --> 00:07:01.428
Thank you for that.'Because God loves beautiful things. He is meticulous in everything He does; He cares about every single detail concerning every single one of you.

00:07:01.429 --> 00:07:09.271
Even your name is on that name card in the center of those plates.

00:07:09.272 --> 00:07:24.843
On my plate, what He was showing me, I saw Brandon Biggs and I saw a translucent-looking lily plate that was beautiful because I love flowers.

00:07:24.844 --> 00:07:34.551
I am a flower person; I love landscaping and flowers. I could spend hours just pulling weeds and making things look beautiful.

00:07:34.552 --> 00:07:50.672
I love flowers of all His creation—it's a big deal for me. I saw that my plate was a lily, and it was pink and beautiful.

00:07:50.673 --> 00:08:03.468
Then the one next to me was white-looking china, and I saw the settings of the forks.

00:08:03.469 --> 00:08:14.159
Then there were some plates down over here that had chopsticks in them because not everybody likes to use a fork.

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:20.159
That's neat! There are some people who like chopsticks. They might say, 'Well, what are we going to eat?'I don't know.

00:08:20.160 --> 00:08:24.888
The Bible says the marriage supper of the Lamb. What is that? I don't know. Maybe we'll eat lamb—I have no idea, folks.

00:08:24.889 --> 00:08:36.915
I just know that there's a reception, and I saw the reception He was preparing for the bride, and it was beautiful.

00:08:36.916 --> 00:08:53.633
There was lace and beautiful things throughout the trees, and there were twinkle lights in that lace, powered by Holy Spirit power, I guess.

00:08:53.634 --> 00:09:07.038
They were like little lightning bugs all inside of this lace, and it was wrapped in tulle in these humongous oak trees, like weeping willows.

00:09:07.039 --> 00:09:12.985
You know how you see those down in New Orleans where the moss is dangling out of those trees?

00:09:12.986 --> 00:09:21.574
It was like that, but there was gorgeous-looking lace in this massive tree next to the table.

00:09:21.575 --> 00:09:32.110
Beautiful! It was a ginormous tree, not some skinny tree. I'm talking about trees with huge trunks.

00:09:32.111 --> 00:09:40.427
They were all in the atmosphere above, wrapped in tulle with little twinkle lights. I could see all of that.

00:09:40.428 --> 00:10:08.878
Then they had flower arrangements on all the tables in crystal vases—beautiful things that fanned out with all kinds of beautiful purples, greens, baby's breath, and beautiful lavender and pink flowers.

00:10:08.879 --> 00:10:16.247
It was done so perfectly. All of it. And they were on all the tables and all the doilies and all of it.

00:10:16.248 --> 00:10:23.154
It was just so like a beautiful, beautiful wedding reception.

00:10:23.154 --> 00:10:33.545
And then I don't want to cut it too short because I always try to tell y'all the things about it, and sometimes I add more to it because I'm like, you know, why hurry?

00:10:33.546 --> 00:10:38.722
Why hurry? You know, if you want to listen to it, fine. If you don't, fine. Fast forward it.

00:10:38.723 --> 00:10:46.719
But it was just beautiful, and it was, as far as I could see, plates and things ready for the people, and they were all okay.

00:10:46.720 --> 00:11:03.113
So one table setting was like this, and the table was all like an old English-looking table, like what you would see in a royal castle, like for the queen, because the table was all like it was all cut out like from a single piece of wood.

00:11:03.114 --> 00:11:06.449
It wasn't like, you know, like we make our cheap-looking tables today.

00:11:06.450 --> 00:11:13.119
We're talking it looked like Prince George, like, you know, like the old beds.

00:11:13.120 --> 00:11:20.278
It looked like the legs on that table were all kind of engraved wood.

00:11:20.279 --> 00:11:26.371
Engraved, and so you could see it, but it was a darker wood, a lighter wood, and then a darker wood.

00:11:26.372 --> 00:11:32.398
And it flushed in like it was just like marble-looking wood. And it was gorgeous.

00:11:32.399 --> 00:11:44.831
And then the Lord showed me the tables, but they went table, aisle, table, aisle, and every single person was just ready for them.

00:11:44.832 --> 00:11:50.583
And it went as far as you could see. I mean, you know, we're talking millions of people here.

00:11:50.584 --> 00:11:54.900
I don't know if it's by shift or whatever. You come by the generation.

00:11:54.901 --> 00:12:00.078
I don't know. How are you going to have the reception for all those people? But heaven's huge.

00:12:00.079 --> 00:12:06.264
But I'm just saying it just, you know, for what I could see, it was for hundreds of thousands.

00:12:06.265 --> 00:12:13.675
I don't know. I don't tell that it was millions of places for what I could see, but it was amazing.

00:12:13.676 --> 00:12:23.659
And then I could see the English Tudor houses. Oh, yeah, the old cobblestone homes.

00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:32.921
And see, in that generation of people, whether it's 1700s or whatever, that was their heart's desire.

00:12:32.922 --> 00:12:39.439
The Bible says that he's making a mansion for every single one of us, and it would be our heart's desire.

00:12:39.440 --> 00:12:45.308
So, your heart's desire in this modern day, your house is going to look a lot different than theirs.

00:12:45.309 --> 00:12:51.359
So if they were in the 1600s and 1500s, their heart's desire was just an English-style house.

00:12:51.360 --> 00:12:57.320
And it was gorgeous, but it was all perfect. The cobblestone on the side of this house was all perfect.

00:12:57.321 --> 00:13:12.449
And I could see it, and it was like going through a downtown, going through an old downtown because there were houses on both sides, and I could see the old roofs, the way they had it.

00:13:12.450 --> 00:13:32.259
And then the streets were gold, and it went up, and there was a curve, and there was grass, beautiful cut grass, perfect grass that was just like manicured like a golf course. Perfect. And they were having parade practice.

00:13:32.260 --> 00:13:58.900
And I said, "Lord, what are y'all doing?"He said, "We're getting ready for the celebration of you coming home."And I saw the banners, the royal banners of people, and it said 'King of Kings'and 'Lord of Lords'on these banners that were written out in gold letters that looked like on a royalty purple, a deep purple with golden letters.

00:13:58.901 --> 00:14:04.051
And it had beautiful tooling on the side, this beautiful like embroidery of gold.

00:14:04.052 --> 00:14:10.660
And it was purple with golden letters that said 'King of Kings'and 'Lord of Lords'.

00:14:10.661 --> 00:14:27.237
And they were standing there, and the people were standing there in their robes, and they had their heavenly garments on, all different styles of clothes, all different styles of outfits, the way they looked.

00:14:27.238 --> 00:14:59.103
Not everybody was the same, but everybody was worshiping, and they were saying, "For he is good and his mercy endures forever, for the Lord is good and his mercy endures forever."And as he was marching down the street on the golden street, Jesus was riding his horse, and he had a crown on his head that looked like it had a white around it with this black-looking leopard stuff, and it went up in purple and gold and went up like this.

00:14:59.104 --> 00:15:15.366
And it had a thing on the top, and he had a purple-looking cloak on with a white embroidery around it, and then he had this beautiful outfit, a robe-like, gown-looking thing, and he was on his horse.

00:15:15.367 --> 00:15:40.559
And his horse bridle, I've said this, it has beautiful jewels all throughout that bridle on that horse's bit going up through, and where he was holding the reins, it was beautiful—the jewels and the sapphires and the pearls and the diamonds and everything was on his bridle and what goes on the horse's chest.

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:46.313
And he rode it up in the spirit realm, and I could see him riding on it, and his horse was beautiful white.

00:15:46.314 --> 00:15:54.258
It was a beautiful-looking, white-looking horse. It was gorgeous.

00:15:54.259 --> 00:16:01.750
It's absolutely gorgeous. And all the people, and you could see confetti in the air.

00:16:01.751 --> 00:16:23.019
Like confetti-like stuff was in the air, and how it was blowing at all times I have no idea because I don't know that celebration, but it was in the atmosphere, and it was on the streets, and it was being shaken like you'd see on New Year's Eve when the ball drops in Times Square and all the confetti is coming, but it was in the air, in the atmosphere.

00:16:23.020 --> 00:16:36.638
Colors and things were moving around as people were walking down, and they were blowing their horns and their trumpets, and they were sounding the praises of him, the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords.

00:16:36.639 --> 00:16:42.882
Beautiful. But the people were excited that we were coming home.

00:16:42.883 --> 00:16:54.232
All our loved ones that have gone on before us, that have passed on, ladies and gentlemen, to be absent from the body is to be present with the Lord. And they are waiting for us.

00:16:54.233 --> 00:17:11.826
They are the great cloud of witnesses that are waiting on us, ladies and gentlemen, that are celebrating our soon return, that Jesus has paid the price for every single one of you to not go to hell.

00:17:11.827 --> 00:17:30.380
Thank you, Jesus. If you just accept him and turn from your sin and your wicked ways, Jesus has paid the price for every single one of you so you can go to heaven with him for eternity. I know a lot of you don't get it.

00:17:30.381 --> 00:17:57.141
There's a lot of you that are so lost, but I pray for you every day that the eyes of your understanding would be enlightened, that you would know the hope of your calling and how much he loves you, that he paid the price for every single one of you to walk in victory, going from glory to glory to glory.

00:17:57.142 --> 00:18:04.573
There was a stream, looked like a bridge, where the parade ended.

00:18:04.574 --> 00:18:16.529
It looked like it went a long way, but I could see the people, and they were lining both sides of the streets waiting for the people, like celebrating, getting ready for the people.

00:18:16.530 --> 00:18:25.542
And there was a bridge, the gold streets, the brick gold streets went over the bridge.

00:18:25.543 --> 00:18:38.942
And there was a stream going through there. And then there was a massive castle that was right in front of it right here.

00:18:38.943 --> 00:18:45.348
A humongous, I'm talking ginormous-looking castle that was over here.

00:18:45.349 --> 00:18:50.399
Now, I don't know whose house that was, but they had big desires.

00:18:50.400 --> 00:18:56.691
Some people, if you only believe for small, you only get small because that was the desire of your heart.

00:18:56.692 --> 00:19:04.563
He's not going to override what you're believing for. What's your chokehold?

00:19:04.564 --> 00:19:09.759
How big is your faith and what you're believing for with God?

00:19:09.760 --> 00:19:16.131
God's limitless, but he will only move at your ability to believe him for it.

00:19:16.132 --> 00:19:23.431
Even in your heart's desires, he doesn't override you. You've got to stretch yourself.

00:19:23.432 --> 00:19:30.325
You've got to learn how to believe God for bigger. Some people have a measure of faith like the scripture.

00:19:30.326 --> 00:19:35.508
Some people have a chokehold where you have to look at your chokehold.

00:19:35.509 --> 00:19:41.250
If I tell you to believe God for a million dollars, you say, "Ah, that's not a big deal."Some people would say that.

00:19:41.251 --> 00:20:00.452
And some people go, "Oh my goodness, that's a lot of money."Some people go, "That's not that big."Then if I say you believe God for $10 million and then you go, "That's,"and then somebody says, "That's not that bad."And then somebody says, "I'm believing God for a hundred million dollars,"and you go, "Woo, wow, $100 million."That's what I'm trying to talk about: your choke point.

00:20:00.453 --> 00:20:16.079
Where does your faith go and you go, you know, where you go, "That's a lot,"you know, versus "That's nothing"? Grow bigger in your capacity to believe God for more.

00:20:16.080 --> 00:20:24.335
Stretch your faith to believe him for exceedingly abundantly above all you dare ask or think, even in the next life.

00:20:24.336 --> 00:20:31.552
Some people, if you think like $1,000, you know, is a lot, you start out where your faith is $100.

00:20:31.553 --> 00:20:37.666
I can believe God for $100. So, you believe $100 ten times. It doesn't make you less than.

00:20:37.667 --> 00:20:44.864
No, I'm just trying to tell you to stretch yourself because I saw houses that were beautiful.

00:20:44.865 --> 00:20:54.119
But I'm not running their house down in heaven by no means, because it makes anything on this earth look like a shack compared to a glorified house.

00:20:54.120 --> 00:21:04.550
But I'm just saying I could see massive castles. Wow. Somebody was believing for a massive castle and they got it. Wow.

00:21:04.551 --> 00:21:13.170
I don't know who it was, but I saw their house and I was like, "Are you kidding me?"That looked like a king's castle, but it wasn't where the Lord stayed.

00:21:13.171 --> 00:21:18.330
It was somebody's house. And this place was massive. It was gorgeous.

00:21:18.331 --> 00:21:22.236
It looked like something out of Cinderella, you know, like a...

00:21:22.236 --> 00:21:29.973
But it was all looking like cobblestone again, you know, the cobblestone, but it was built like that all on the side of this hill.

00:21:29.974 --> 00:21:37.076
And I could see trees around it and some, like, not like, you know, like that peat moss, like moss stuff growing on it.

00:21:37.077 --> 00:21:40.556
Gorgeous looking like greenery and stuff around this castle.

00:21:40.557 --> 00:21:49.423
And it was on this hill above the golden street and it was over like over here from where they're having the parade.

00:21:49.424 --> 00:21:56.645
But it's just it's overwhelming how much he loves us and how much he's preparing a place for us.

00:21:56.646 --> 00:22:03.087
And our great cloud of witnesses, our loved ones, our relatives are watching and waiting for us.

00:22:03.088 --> 00:22:07.687
And Jesus Christ is coming, ladies and gentlemen. He's coming. Exciting!

00:22:07.688 --> 00:22:15.951
And we are going to be in paradise forever and ever and ever, singing praises to the King.

00:22:15.952 --> 00:22:24.398
It's a massive place, heaven is, and we will call it home. And he's going to make a new heaven and a new earth.

00:22:24.399 --> 00:22:43.759
And we've got a thousand-year reign that we will rule and reign with him, and I'm telling you, there are great days ahead in our glorified bodies, giving praise to the King of Kings and the Lord of Lords.

00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:50.693
And I'm telling you, he is worthy of all our praise. He loves us and he is amazing.

00:22:50.694 --> 00:23:02.953
He's an amazing God. So, you know, that's what I had, that part of this to tell you all today. I look forward to it all the time.

00:23:02.954 --> 00:23:10.791
I look forward to it because there's loved ones over there that I miss: my grandfather and my grandma.

00:23:10.792 --> 00:23:23.210
There's people over there that you go, "Huh, I know they're waiting on us."And when we get there, I wonder if we'll recognize them that much because of how young they'll look in their glorified bodies.

00:23:23.211 --> 00:23:32.347
You'll go, "Wow, you look great,"you know? Yeah. You know, because when I saw myself, I looked really great.

00:23:32.348 --> 00:23:43.712
I had good hair. I was like, "Hey, I've got good hair. Thank you, Lord."So, you look the same as always, babe.

00:23:43.713 --> 00:23:54.442
And I think in your glorified body, you look the same to me. But I mean seriously, it's amazing what the Lord's going to do.

00:23:54.443 --> 00:24:04.108
So, but you know, just now we have to be serious about some things about the war and the things that I've seen coming.

00:24:04.109 --> 00:24:19.054
You know, there's a lot of good that President Trump's wanting to do, but the devil is going to try to throw a monkey wrench as much as he can to delay things and cause things not to happen because he knows his time is short.

00:24:19.055 --> 00:24:24.671
So, he is working at full capacity even when we're sleeping.

00:24:24.672 --> 00:24:52.249
He's like, "I'm going to try to kill, steal, and destroy and make sure that a lot of you don't make it to get that house, to get that paradise."Because he was there and he got kicked out, and he is ticked off that every single one of you have the opportunity to get what he had, and he can't have it no more in the presence of the great God Jehovah for the rest of our lives.

00:24:52.250 --> 00:25:09.430
And his plan is the lake of fire, hell, and on earth. He's going to be burning for eternity forever and ever and ever with every one of his little devils that tormented and destroyed people's lives.

00:25:09.431 --> 00:25:20.205
Their eternity is hell. Hell, hell. And I am so grateful that God, you know, that his time is coming short. It's over. Yes.

00:25:20.206 --> 00:25:31.272
And he is freaking out right now because he knows, and he's trying to speed things up so he can try to cause as many of you to go to hell with him as he can.

00:25:31.273 --> 00:25:35.205
That's his whole plan. He does not care. He knows his time's up.

00:25:35.206 --> 00:25:42.857
He knows he can't stop it. But what gets God the most? What does God find valuable?

00:25:42.858 --> 00:25:49.236
What does God see that's valuable? Is it the gold? No. He makes streets out of it.

00:25:49.237 --> 00:25:55.251
It's concrete to him. Is it the diamonds? No. He makes bridles out of them for horses.

00:25:55.252 --> 00:26:00.941
What does he find that's important? It's you and me, ladies and gentlemen.

00:26:00.942 --> 00:26:06.830
We're what's important to him. He sent his one and only son to die for you.

00:26:06.831 --> 00:26:12.255
The most beautiful thing that he could ever do was give his life for you freely.

00:26:12.256 --> 00:26:21.999
He didn't do it grudgingly. He did it because he wanted to. It says he became sickness for us.

00:26:22.000 --> 00:26:37.794
He became poverty for us so that we don't have to have it, that we don't have to walk in hell, depression, anxiety, fear, torment of all kinds.

00:26:37.795 --> 00:26:44.137
He became that. He took it on himself. He had to receive it by faith.

00:26:44.138 --> 00:26:52.196
He had to receive sickness and disease by faith on his body because he was Holy Ghost all the way around.

00:26:52.197 --> 00:26:57.677
He walked without measure. But he didn't know sickness. He didn't know disease.

00:26:57.678 --> 00:27:03.359
He didn't know sin. So he became sin for us. He became sickness.

00:27:03.360 --> 00:27:08.210
He had to receive that by faith by yielding himself to it and saying, "I became it.

00:27:08.211 --> 00:27:16.295
I have to do this. I'm going to take it."And then it came all on him willingly. He willingly did it for you and me.

00:27:16.296 --> 00:27:28.783
And the thing that the devil wants to try to do the most is to get you to believe a lie that he doesn't love you, that he doesn't have a plan for you, that he doesn't care anything about you.

00:27:28.784 --> 00:27:40.588
"Oh, God's mad at you. Yeah, he's punishing you. He put this sickness on you."He can't give you something, ladies and gentlemen, that he doesn't have in heaven.

00:27:40.589 --> 00:27:50.319
There is no sickness in heaven. There is no poverty. Trust me, I've seen the houses. There is no poverty in heaven. So, he can't.

00:27:50.320 --> 00:27:57.070
